When selecting a specific branch in bitbucket, the search box disappears (This is the search box to filter commits, not the one in the header to find a repository).

I expect that box to be present to further filter the commits.

@Liam: Please put the box back.

_Preconditions_
Create a a new disciple;
_STR_
1. Click the button "Ученики" on the panel;
2. Select the newly created student, f.e. "Burla";
3. On the field "Данные ученика" click on the button "Редактировать данные";
4.  In the "тип"  click on the any  radiobutton,  f.e."звонок";
5. In the "Источник"  click on the radiobutton "Промо-код" and select any value, f.e. "300" and "1";
6. Click on the button "Сохранить".
_Actual result_
In the "Источник" specified promo code does not show.
_Expected result_
In the "Источник" given promo code affect.
_Comment_
But if promo code in the "источник" had already been given, and it just fix to another, then it is displayed correctly.
_Postconditions_
Delete the pupil.

When I enter all of the required information into the [payment details|https://btconsulting.atlassian.net/admin/billing/paymentdetails] page and click the Send button, I get an error message
{noformat}
Something went wrong while trying to update your payment details. Please try again.
{noformat}
with no further information given.

I am aware of [CLOUD-7786], but am uncertain of whether it's the same.  First, it's stopping me from being able to make payments, so it's not a Minor priority; second, the description says to log in to JIRA, which may be the same facility but I can't be sure; third, it mentions log details that I haven't been able to find.
